The National Leader of the All Progressives Congress (APC), Asiwaju Bola Ahmed Tinubu, on Friday officially endorsed the Lagos State Governor Babajide Sanwo-Olu, and his deputy, Obafemi Hamzat, for a second term in office. This was disclosed by Sanwo-Olu’s Chief Press Secretary, Gboyega Akosila, in a tweet which had a video of Tinubu raising the hands of the governor and his deputy. The tweet read, “Asiwaju @officialABAT officially endorsed Governor @jidesanwoolu and deputy @drobafemihamzat for second term.” -Advertisement- Recall that on 29, April 2022, Sanwo-Olu had purchased the APC party’s N50 million governorship form to run for a second term in office.